quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  14,43,They hasten forward in fear; their heads upraised in supplication; their looks riveted; and their hearts a blank. Warn men therefore of the day when the punishment shall overtake them
  14,44,"And when the evil doers shall say, \"O our Lord! respite us yet a little while: To thy call will we make answer; thine Apostles will we follow.\" \"Did ye not once swear that no change should befal you"
  14,45,Yet ye dwelt in the dwellings of those who were the authors of their undoing and it was made plain to you how we had dealt with them; and we held them up to you as examples
  14,46,"They plotted their plots: but God could master their plots, even though their plots had been so powerful as to move the mountains"
  14,47,"Think not then that God will fail his promise to his Apostles: aye! God is mighty, and Vengeance is His"
  14,48,"On the day when the Earth shall be changed into another Earth, and the Heavens also, men shall come forth unto God, the Only, the Victorious"
  14,49,And thou shalt see the wicked on that day linked together in chains
  14,50,"Their garments of pitch, and fire shall enwrap their faces"
  14,51,that God may reward every soul as it deserveth; verily God is prompt to reckon
  14,52,"This is a message for mankind, that they may thereby be warned: and that they may know that there is but one God; and that men of understanding may ponder it"